## Fix: synced table API requires database_project + database_branch for Autoscaling

### Context
After the previous fix (omitting `database_instance_name`), the Lakebase API rejected
the POST with: `Must specify either database instance name or both database project and
branch!`.  The API now enforces that callers either supply a provisioned `database_instance_name`
or the Autoscaling pair `database_project` + `database_branch`.  Passing only the project
name as `database_instance_name` caused the control-plane to use the project's default
(production) branch instead of the configured `demo` branch.

### Changes

1. **`src/back/core/databricks/LakebaseAuth.py`**
   - Added `branch_name` property: parses the branch segment from
     `_endpoint_resource` (path format `projects/<proj>/branches/<branch>/endpoints/<ep>`).
     Triggers resolution lazily via `instance_name` so it works for both
     `PGHOST`-based (Apps) and `LAKEBASE_PROJECT`+`LAKEBASE_BRANCH`-based (local) setups.

2. **`src/back/core/graphdb/lakebase/SyncedTableManager.py`**
   - `__init__`: added `project_name` and `branch_name` keyword args (stored as
     `self._project` / `self._branch`).
   - `_build_synced_table_dict`: emits `database_project` + `database_branch` when
     both are available; falls back to `database_instance_name` (project-only) when
     branch is unknown.
   - `_build_synced_table_sdk`: tries `database_project` + `database_branch`; falls
     back silently to `database_instance_name` for older SDK versions that lack these
     fields (`TypeError` guard).

3. **`src/back/core/graphdb/GraphDBFactory.py`**
   - `_build_synced_manager`: resolves `auth.instance_name` (project) and
     `auth.branch_name` (branch), passes both to `SyncedTableManager`.  Added
     INFO-level log so the resolved values are visible in App logs.

4. **`tests/test_synced_table_manager.py`**
   - `_make_manager`: passes `project_name` and `branch_name` to the manager.
   - `test_ensure_creates_when_missing`: asserts `mgr._project` / `mgr._branch`
     instead of checking for absent keys in the payload kwargs.

### Modified files
- `src/back/core/databricks/LakebaseAuth.py`
- `src/back/core/graphdb/lakebase/SyncedTableManager.py`
- `src/back/core/graphdb/GraphDBFactory.py`
- `tests/test_synced_table_manager.py`

### Test result
31/31 passed (`test_synced_table_manager.py` + `test_build_pipeline_streaming.py`)

