## Feature: Lakebase Objects panel in Graph DB Settings

### Context
When a schema (or table/view) in Lakebase is owned by the app's service principal, the
human user cannot drop it directly because Postgres requires you to own the object.
A dedicated panel in Settings > Graph DB now lists all user-visible objects in the connected
Lakebase database and lets the current user drop any object they own — without having to open
a psql shell.

### Changes

1. **`src/back/objects/domain/SettingsService.py`**
   - `graph_engine_lakebase_objects_result(database, session_mgr, settings)`: queries
     `pg_catalog.pg_namespace`, `pg_catalog.pg_tables`, and `pg_catalog.pg_views` to return
     all non-system schemas, tables, and views with their owner; also exposes `current_user`.
   - `graph_engine_lakebase_drop_object_result(kind, schema, name, database, ...)`: executes
     `DROP SCHEMA … CASCADE`, `DROP TABLE`, or `DROP VIEW` with quoted identifiers; never
     raises — failures return `success=False`.

2. **`src/api/routers/internal/settings.py`**
   - `GET /settings/graph-engine/lakebase-objects`: calls `graph_engine_lakebase_objects_result`.
   - `POST /settings/graph-engine/lakebase-drop-object`: calls `graph_engine_lakebase_drop_object_result`
     with body `{ kind, schema, name, database }`.

3. **`src/front/templates/settings.html`**
   - New `<details id="lakebaseObjectsDetails">` block inside `#lakebaseGraphPanel`, below the
     health section; contains a "Load objects" button and a `#lakebaseObjectsResult` container.

4. **`src/front/static/config/js/settings.js`**
   - `loadLakebaseObjects()`: fetches the objects endpoint and renders a grouped table (Type /
     Schema / Name / Owner / Action); Drop buttons are shown only for objects owned by `current_user`.
   - `dropLakebaseObject(kind, schema, name)`: native `confirm()` → POST → `showNotification` +
     reload; error surfaced inline.
   - `window._lkDropObject` shim exposes the function to inline `onclick` handlers in the
     dynamically rendered table.

### Modified files
- `src/back/objects/domain/SettingsService.py`
- `src/api/routers/internal/settings.py`
- `src/front/templates/settings.html`
- `src/front/static/config/js/settings.js`

### Test result
1498 passed, pre-existing failures unrelated to this change (dtwin.py Python 3.9 union-type
syntax blocks the full app-import; those failures existed before this commit).

